# Integration test: IIcx Boot
# Runs the Universal ROM far enough to exit RAM-test and reach the floppy
# / question-mark icon screen, then verifies the machine identified
# itself as IIcx (PA6=1, PB3=1) and exposes a 640x480 NuBus video display.

# 500M instructions is enough to clear the RAM test and reach the
# Slot Manager phase where the JMFB driver's PrimaryInit runs.  The
# matching SE/30 boot test uses 335M; IIcx takes longer because the
# Slot Manager scans NuBus space.
scheduler.run 100000000

# Machine-ID bits resolved correctly: ROM identified the IIcx.
assert ${machine.id == "iicx"} "machine.id != iicx"

# NuBus card seated in slot $9 with a 640x480 default mode.
assert ${screen.width == 640} "screen.width != 640 (NuBus card not seated?)"
assert ${screen.height == 480} "screen.height != 480"

# JMFB card driver registered.  nubus.cards() returns a list of card-id
# strings; we just check it's non-empty (truthy).
assert $(nubus.cards()) "nubus.cards() returned empty"

# Real screen content must be present.  A zero checksum means the OS
# never painted anything to the framebuffer (PrimaryInit didn't run, or
# our display descriptor isn't pointing at painted VRAM).
assert ${screen.checksum() != 0} "screen.checksum == 0 — JMFB never painted"

quit
